communications.subject: California Public Records Act Request: Necropsy Reports
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the California Public Records Act, I hereby request the following records:

I am seeking documents related to Neuralink's work with the University of California, Davis’s California National Primate Research Center (CNPRC).  Specifically I am seeking any Animal Death Records related to Neuralink research, Necropsy reports related to Neuralink research and UNIVERSITY SERVICES AGREEMENTS with Neuralink.  Please provide records from 01/01/2020 until the date this request is processed. These records are similar to those the University produced for the Physician's Committee in 2021.

Thanks
Dhruv Mehrotra

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 10 calendar days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Dhruv Mehrotra

title: FOIA Request for Proposals Submitted and Contracts Awarded Pertaining to to RFP for Contratc Paramedic/Firefighter for Village of Western Springs

communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Illinois Freedom of Information Act., I hereby request the following records:

Please provide copies of all proposals submitted in response to the RFP for Contract Paramedic/Firefighters issued by the Village of Western Springs. In addition, please supply a copy of the Contract that was awarded to the Company who was awarded the contract as a result of the RFP. Finally, please provide copies of any and all E-Mail correspondence to/from vendors who submitted a proposal in response to the RFP as well as any E-Mail messages or any/all other correpondeance or documents between Village of Western Spring staff that pertain to the discussion and/or evaluation of proposals submitted in responde to the RFP

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 5 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Law Dog

communications.subject: Colorado Open Records Act Request: Book Complaints: Douglas County Libraries
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Colorado Open Records Act, (CORA) C.R.S. § 24-72-201 to 206, I hereby request the following records:

Copies of written and electronic complaints and challenges for removal, reclassification, or other reconsideration of instructional and library materials including books, ebooks, and audiobooks from January 1, 2000 (or as early as available) to the present, as well as records, petitions, correspondence, and the outcomes related to these challenges. These complaint forms may be categorized as “Request for reconsideration of materials”, "Review of instructional materials" or “Request for review of building level recommendation”. These are sometimes referred to as “book challenges.”

As we believe these records will benefit the public interest and inform public understanding of book challenges across the U.S., we request any fees associated with this request be waived. We are planning to make our findings publicly available. If fees cannot be waived, please inform me in advance. Please know that I am a member of the media, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

If possible, I would appreciate the corresponding records shared via email with text documents or clear PDFs. If you cannot reply electronically, please let me know and I can provide a mailing address. If you expect a significant delay in responding to this request, please contact me with information about when I might expect copies or the ability to inspect the requested records.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 3 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Emma Rubin

title: Public records request: positive COVID-19 cases from 11/1/22 through 11/30/22

communications.subject: California Public Records Act Request: Public records request: positive COVID-19 cases from 11/1/22 through 11/30/22
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the California Public Records Act, I hereby request the following records:

Documents showing the cumulative number of positive COVID-19 cases among students and staff at each RUSD school site, facility and department, from November 1, 2022 through November 30, 2022.

Such documents may include but may not be limited to: spreadsheets, databases, charts, tables, infographics, slide decks, reports, emails and other records, electronic or otherwise.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 10 calendar days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Justin Beck
